SUMMARY:Practical Spanish 2
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nIn this class you will continue to build on the knowledge 
 acquired in Practical Spanish 1 or Spanish 1A. You will expand your 
 vocabulary and continue to practice and add to your repertoire of useful 
 expressions.\n\nTopics covered:\n\n\n	Additional conversation/questions- 
 ordering food/ shopping/making a reservation/airport/train station\; asking 
 and talk about likes and dislikes\;  locating buildings or 
 monuments\n	Making polite requests\n	Interrogative adjectives- 
 Qué/Cómo/Cuándo/Dónde/Quién/Por qué\n	Forming questions\n	More 
 ar/ir/er regular and irregular verbs\n	Gustar/IOP\n	Ask and tell 
 time\n	Possessive adjectives and different ways of showing possession (His 
 book/John’s book)\n	Weather\n	Idiomatic expressions with Tener\n	Contrast 
 and apply the use of Ser/ Estar.\n	Culture/Food/Holidays/Traditions\n	All 
 related vocabulary\n\n\n\nPrerequisite: Completion of Practical Spanish 1\, 
 Spanish 1A or equivalent.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Classroom\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School, Language
UID:LibCal-10306-15673098
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15673098
END:VEVENT
