SUMMARY:Bus Trip: Philadelphia Flower Show
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to 
 register.\n\nNo refunds. Registration deadline: February 12. The 
 award-winning PHS Philadelphia Flower Show is a one-of-a-kind marquee event 
 known the globe over for its exquisite and immersive floral exhibits\, 
 world-class plant competitions\, family-friendly activities\, educational 
 offerings\, and shopping.  This year's theme is Rooted: Origins of American 
 Gardening\, and celebrates the stories that ground us in gardening\, 
 whether it’s the nostalgia of a grandparent’s garden\, a beloved family 
 recipe that begins with the bright scent of freshly picked herbs and 
 vegetables\, or the heritage traditions that shape how we plant\, grow\, 
 and gather. You will explore the show at your leisure until bus pick up at 
 approximately 4 pm. \n Lunch is not included. We encourage you to find an 
 exciting meal at the nearby Reading Market or concession stands on site.
LOCATION:Montclair - Offsite\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
