SUMMARY:MILL @ MPL: Taste of Tai Chi
DESCRIPTION:Note: This is a class run through the MILL. Please register 
 through their website here.\n\nT'ai Chi Ch'uan is a 1000 year old art of 
 mind-body health and energy cultivation. “A Taste of Tai Chi” 
 introduces students to the 12-posture Yang-style Short Form of Master Bow 
 Sim Mark and is designed for students of all ages and levels of physical 
 ability. No prior experience with T'ai Chi is necessary. The health 
 benefits of T'ai Chi include balance\, flexibility\, strength\, 
 immune-system support\, and stress relief.\n\nLEWIS FREEMAN studied the 
 “Taste of T’ai Chi” form with Don Madison (Dragon T'ai Chi Ch'uan 
 Association) and achieved the level of Assistant Teacher in July 2019. He 
 previously studied the Yang-style short form at Long River T’aiChi Circle 
 in Manhattan in the 1990s. When he's not practicing T’ai Chi\, Lewis 
 teaches at Fordham University as Senior Lecturer in Communication and Media 
 Studies and also consults for businesses and organizations.\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Fitness
