SUMMARY:Black Women in Biopic: Queen of Katwe (2016)
DESCRIPTION:Queen of Katwe (2016) | PG\, 124mins\n\nThis biopic of Ugandan 
 chess prodigy Phiona Mutesi traces her journey from the slums of Katwe\, 
 where she is forced to abandon her schooling at the age of nine\, to the 
 upper echelons of the chess world after she develops an interest in the 
 game at a youth-outreach program. Watch the trailer here.\n\n\nSeating for 
 the film is first come\, first served. No registration is required.
