SUMMARY:Frank Lloyd Wright: Is Less Really More? NEW
DESCRIPTION:This is a paid Adult School class. Click here to register on 
 the Adult School website.\n\nOne of America's most celebrated and 
 influential architects\, Frank Lloyd Wright got involved in the effort to 
 standardize housing and make it more efficient toward the end of his 
 career\, after World War II. His version was the Usonian house\, which 
 relied on economy of scale\, what he called "the honest materials" of 
 wood\, stone and glass\, and which highlighted the natural setting. Looking 
 back\, these Usonian houses are the absolute opposite of the McMansions so 
 many favor today. What can we learn from the Usonian house\, for good and 
 for bad?
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Conference Room\, Montclair Public Library
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Adult School":MAILTO:adultschool@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult School
UID:LibCal-10306-15711443
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15711443
