SUMMARY:Make It Rhyme: Empowering Young Poets (Recommended Grades 3-5)
DESCRIPTION:A weekly introduction to poetry covering haiku\, sonnet\, blank 
 & free verse\, are covered in depth. Kids will learn historical 
 significance\, structure\, and grammatical conventions. We'll write our own 
 poetry and express ourselves in new ways. With excerpts from The Odyssey\, 
 Ozymandias\, Jabberwocky and more serving as writing inspiration. Kids will 
 also make art based on their poems\, further demonstrating their 
 creativity. Facilitated by poet Jack Jerow. Registration recommended for 
 reminders.\n\n
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Storytime Room
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
