SUMMARY:Mah Jongg: Spring Open Play
DESCRIPTION:PLEASE NOTE: You must sign up for EACH INDIVIDUAL SESSION. 
 Signing up for one session does not register you for any following 
 classes.\n\nThe Mah Jongg Meetup provides a weekly opportunity for players 
 to continue practicing their established skills\, sharpen their 
 strategies\, build confidence at the game table\, and socialize with fellow 
 Mah Jongg players!\n\nThe library will provide five reserved tables in the 
 cafe! \n\nNOTE: Attendees should bring their personal sets to this meetup 
 and should already have an understanding of the Mah Jongg game. Attendees 
 should bring their 2025 or 2026 National Mah Jongg League card to the 
 meetup. Bringing an additional set is encouraged!\n\n*Note: There will be a 
 limited number of Mah Jongg sets available on a first-come\, first-served 
 basis.\n\nIf you're new to the game\, or don't feel comfortable sitting at 
 a table and playing with others at a similar level\, please register for a 
 Beginner class by clicking here.\n\n \n\nIMPORTANT 
 REMINDERS:\n\n\n	Students should have taken Beginner Mah Jongg or have 
 equivalent knowledge and experience. \n	Students should bring the 2025 
 National Mah Jongg League card to Open Play.\n\n
