SUMMARY:Memory Café - A Dementia-Friendly Social Gathering
DESCRIPTION:For adults with dementia and their caregivers\, this event 
 offers a welcoming\, safe\, calming space for socializing\, music\, art and 
 reminiscing every month.\n\n\nA “Memory Café” is a dementia-friendly 
 social gathering for individuals with early-stage memory loss or mild 
 cognitive decline and their care givers.\n\nThe meetings will be held in a 
 safe and comfortable environment where people can interact and socialize 
 with others having similar experiences. At the gatherings participants can 
 get support in a non-judgmental setting\, while enjoying the benefits of 
 music for the brain.\n\nThe meetings will be run by Lisy Espindola\, LCSW 
 and Kim McLennon\, MSW and music therapist. Lunch and/or snacks will be 
 served.\n\nThis is a joint program between Lifelong Montclair at the 
 Township of Montclair and the Montclair Public Library.\n\nAttendance is 
 free but registration is required. Questions? Call 973-744-3278.\n\nTo stay 
 informed\, sign up for one or all of our eNewsletters\, click 
 here.\n\nPhotographs may be taken during our programs and events for 
 promotional purposes such as social media and e-newsletters. If you do not 
 wish to have your photograph taken please let us know before the event.
LOCATION:Montclair Main - Auditorium
ORGANIZER;CN="Montclair Library":MAILTO:events@montclairlibrary.org
CATEGORIES:Adult Services, Health & Wellness
UID:LibCal-10306-15411627
URL:https://bccls.libcal.com/event/15411627
